\title{cirBEM: Beta Regression Cosinor Models for Circadian Methylation Analysis}
\description{
Fits cosinor-based beta regression models for detecting circadian rhythmicity in DNA methylation array data. Supports fixed-effects (cross-sectional) and mixed-effects (repeated measures) designs with configurable period. Implements empirical Bayes shrinkage of the beta distribution precision parameter across CpG sites, analogous to limma's moderated variance, to improve genome-wide inference. Provides amplitude, phase, and MESOR estimation on both logit-link and response scales.
